{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox News event | image = | caption = | image_size = | date = 2014 | time = | place = [[Ohio]], United States | notes = [[Lawsuit]] }}
The '''Jennifer Cramblett incident''' took place in [[Ohio]], United States in 2014, when Jennifer Cramblett, a [[White people|white]] woman in a lesbian relationship,<ref>{{cite web|date=October 1, 2014|title=Lawsuit: Wrong sperm delivered to lesbian couple|author=Rodriguez, Meredith|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-sperm-donor-lawsuit-met-20140930-story.html}}</ref> gave birth to a [[Multiracial Americans|multiracial]] female child. Cramblett had requested a [[sperm donation|sperm donor]] from a [[Caucasian race|Caucasian]] man and instead was impregnated by the sperm donated by an [[African Americans|African American]] man.<ref name=A>{{cite web|title=White woman sues sperm bank—again—after getting black man's sperm|author=Mullin, Joe|date=April 25, 2016|work=[[Ars Technica]]|url=https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2016/04/white-woman-sues-sperm-bankagainafter-getting-black-mans-sperm/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=White woman sues sperm bank after she mistakenly gets black donor's sperm|author=Bever, Lindsey|date=October 2, 2014|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/10/02/white-woman-sues-sperm-bank-after-she-mistakenly-gets-black-donors-sperm/|work=[[The Washington Post]]}}</ref><ref name=NYT>{{cite web|title=Sperm Banks Accused of Losing Samples and Lying About Donors|author=Lewin, Tamar|date=July 21, 2016|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/22/us/sperm-banks-accused-of-losing-samples-and-lying-about-donors.html}}</ref>
The incident made national headlines and Cramblett and her [[domestic partnership|domestic partner]] Amanda Zinkon<ref name=RN>{{cite web|url=https://rewire.news/article/2014/10/10/black-children-need-safe-healthy-environments-lawsuits-sperm-donors/|publisher=[[Rewire.News]]|title=Black Children Need Safe and Healthy Environments, Not Lawsuits About Sperm Donors|date=October 10, 2014|author=Dixon, Briana}}</ref> filed a lawsuit against the [[sperm bank]] which they eventually lost.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Ohio Sperm-Bank Controversy: A New Case for Reparations?|author=McKnight, Matthew|date=October 14, 2014|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/ohio-sperm-bank-controversy-new-case-reparations|work=[[The New Yorker]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Woman accidentally impregnated with black man's sperm has legal case dismissed|date=September 5, 2015|agency=[[Associated Press]]|location=Ohio|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/sep/05/judge-dismisses-white-woman-lawsuit-black-sperm-donation|work=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2014/oct/03/sperm-donot-lawsuit-racism-eugenics-lesbian-couple-black-donor|work=The Guardian|date=October 3, 2014|author=Bindel, Julie|title=Designer babies? It looks like racism and eugenics to me}}</ref>
In the law suit Cramblett said she the incident was "an unplanned transracial parent-child relationship for which she was not, and is not, prepared."<ref name=A/>
Cramblett also claimed the law suit was "not about race".<ref name=HP>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/10/02/black-sperm-lawsuit_n_5922180.html|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=October 2, 2014|title=White Woman Who Sued Sperm Bank Over Black Baby Says It's Not About Race|author=Bellware, Kim}}</ref>
