{{DISPLAYTITLE:Open Britain}} {{Infobox organization | name = Open Britain | native_name = | native_name_lang = | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | logo = Open Britain logo.png | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = Keep [[United Kingdom|Britain]] in the [[European Union]] Single market | predecessor = [[Britain Stronger in Europe]] | merged = | formation = <!-- use {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | founder = | founding_location = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | headquarters = Millbank Tower, 21-24 Millbank, London, England, SW1P 4QP | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | membership = | membership_year = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = Executive Director | leader_name = James McGrory<ref name="EveningStandard_26Oct2017">{{cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/outer-london-families-hit-by-brexit-squeeze-as-pay-rises-just-12-per-cent-a3668566.html |title=Outer London families hit by Brexit squeeze as pay rises just 1.2 per cent |work=London Evening Standard |date=26 October 2017 |last=Prynn |first=Jonathan |accessdate=5 November 2017}}</ref> | leader_title2 = Directors | leader_name2 = Joseph Carberry, [[Trevor Phillips]], [[Richard Reed]], [[Peter Mandelson|Lord Peter Mandelson]], [[Roland Rudd]], [[June Sarpong]], [[Will Straw|William Straw]], Daniel Gieve, [[Michael Rake|Sir Michael Rake]] <ref>Companies House https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/09641190/officers</ref> | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = [[People's Vote]] | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | endowment_year = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|www.open-britain.co.uk}} | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }} {{United Kingdom in the European Union}} '''Open Britain''' is British pro-[[European Union]] campaign group set up in the [[Aftermath of the United Kingdom European Union membership referendum, 2016|aftermath of the 2016 European Union referendum]].<ref>{{cite news | last = Dallison | first = Paul |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/remain-mps-launch-pro-europe-campaign-group/ |title=Remain MPs launch pro-Europe campaign group |work=[[Politico Europe|Politico]] |date=2 September 2016 |accessdate=27 August 2018}}</ref>
== Background == Open Britain defines itself as campaigning for the United Kingdom to be open and inclusive, open for business, open to trade and investment, open to talent and hard work, open to Europe and to the world.<ref>{{cite web|author=Open Britain |url=http://www.open-britain.co.uk/about | website = open-britain.co.uk |title=About |publisher=Open Britain |date= |accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref> It is also campaigning for Britain to remain in the Single Market as part of the outcome of the [[Brexit negotiations]].<ref>{{cite news | last1 = Asthana | first1 = Anushka | last2 = Mason | first2 = Rowena | last3 = Syal | first3 = Rajeev | author-link1=Anushka Asthana |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/oct/11/government-adviser-leaving-eu-customs-union-uk-25bn |title=Brexit adviser: leaving EU customs union will cost UK £25bn a year |work=The Guardian |date=11 October 2016 |accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>
In October 2016, Open Britain launched a 'Write to Remain' letter-writing campaign directed at [[Theresa May]] asking her to guarantee the right of EU nationals to stay in the UK.<ref>{{cite news | last = Mason | first = Rowena |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2016/oct/13/letter-campaign-theresa-may-eu-nationals-stay-in-uk |title=Letter-writing campaign urges Theresa May to let EU nationals stay in UK |work=The Guardian |date=13 October 2016 | accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>
The individuals involved in the campaign group include former Ministers [[Pat McFadden (British politician)|Pat McFadden]] (Labour) and [[Norman Lamb]] (Liberal Democrat).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.open-britain.co.uk/new_campaign_group_open_britain_launches_to_fight_for_best_possible_eu_deal_for_britain|title=New campaign group, Open Britain, launches to fight for best possible EU deal for Britain|last=Open Britain | website = open-britain.co.uk|publisher=Open Britain|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref> Conservatives [[Anna Soubry]], [[Nicky Morgan]], and [[Dominic Grieve]] cut their ties with Open Britain in April 2017 after it began to campaign against the re-election of anti-EU members of parliament, mostly Conservatives.<ref>{{cite news | last = Walker | first = Peter |title=Pro-EU Tories quit Open Britain over plans to oust Brexit-backing MPs |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/apr/25/pro-eu-tories-quit-open-britain-over-plans-to-oust-brexit-backing-mps |work=The Guardian |date=25 April 2017 |accessdate=13 July 2017}}</ref>
Open Britain continues to campaign in collaboration with other major pro-European campaign groups such as Britain for Europe and [[European Movement UK]]. It joined [[People's Vote]] in April 2018 to campaign for another referendum.<ref>{{cite news | last = Porritt | first = Richard | title = Campaign launched to push for People’s Vote | url = http://www.theneweuropean.co.uk/top-stories/second-brexit-vote-campaign-launch-1-5476745 | work = [[The New European]] | date = 15 April 2018 | access-date = 17 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Staff writer | title = Launch of the new national People’s Vote campaign | url = https://www.open-britain.co.uk/launch_of_the_new_national_people_s_vote_campaign | website = open-britain.co.uk | publisher = Open Britain | date = 15 April 2018 | access-date = 17 April 2018}}</ref>
