'''Party princess''' is a term associated with a person who entertains children at birthday parties, often dressed as different [[Disney]] I characters. <ref> [https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/confessions-of-a-professional-disney-princess_us_5a301e25e4b01598ac48a202 Huffington Post Article]</ref> <ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/meet-the-real-disney-princess-impersonators-of-new-york_us_5783b028e4b0c590f7ea1d19 " Meet the Real Disney Princess of New York]</ref> The most common party princesses costumes are [[Elsa (Disney) |Elsa]], [[Cinderella (Disney character)|Cinderella]], [[Sleeping Beauty (Disney character)|Sleeping Beauty]] and [[Ariel (Disney)|The Little Mermaid]]. Party princesses generally perform at private birthday parties for young girls - they sing, dance and play with the girls, all-while maintaining a party theme based on the character they're dressed up as.<ref> [http://www.businessinsider.com/what-its-really-like-to-be-a-part-time-princess-2016-1 Business Insider Article] </ref> <ref> [https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/for-professional-princesses-birthday-party-gigs-are-big-business/2013/04/26/c15035d4-a848-11e2-b029-8fb7e977ef71_story.html?noredirect=on For Professional Princesses, Birthday Party Gigs Are a Big Business] </ref> <ref> [https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/2016/07/21/party-princesses-change-with-times/WiIUUXIzw25Hk3Mf6m5sRN/story.html Party princesses change with the times] </ref>
