{{Infobox music festival | name =Piedra Roja | image = | caption = | location =[[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]], [[Chile]] | years_active =1970 | founders = | dates =10 - 12 October 1970 | genre = [[Rock music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website = }} '''Piedra Roja''' was a music festival in [[Chile]] noted as an expression of the [[Hippie|hippie counterculture]] in [[South America]].<ref>[http://www.inedit-nescafe.cl/muestra-2011/competencia-nacional-2011/piedra-roja/ 2011 website on Piedra Roja]</ref> Following the success of [[Woodstock]], a similar music festival was held in [[Chile]] between 10 and 12 October 1970 in the eastern area of [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]]. Among others, the following bands performed in the festival: [[Aguaturbia]], [[Los Blops]], [[Lágrima Seca]] and [[Los Jaivas]]. Similarly to [[Woodstock]], chaos marked the festival, involving problems with sound, drugs and delinquency. The festival showed for the first time that the young population in Chile during that time was a group to reckon with. It also showed the increasing social tension that would end in the ascension of [[Pinochet]].{{cn|date=May 2015}}
